对于已经创建的项目，右键项目根目录，选择"Add Framework Support"(如下图)可添加Maven。

<img class="alignnone  wp-image-9" src="https://wth687.files.wordpress.com/2016/10/screen-shot-2016-10-19-at-20-01-09.png" alt="screen-shot-2016-10-19-at-20-01-09" width="421" height="117" />

After added Maven to our project, a new file called "pom.xml" will be added to our project, too. This is the config file for Maven. Open it.

Add following codes to this file and the dependencies will be added.

Example:
<pre>&lt;properties&gt;
    &lt;maven.compiler.source&gt;1.8&lt;/maven.compiler.source&gt;
    &lt;maven.compiler.target&gt;1.8&lt;/maven.compiler.target&gt;
&lt;/properties&gt;

&lt;dependencies&gt;
    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;junit&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;junit&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;4.12&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;
&lt;/dependencies&gt;</pre>

First add JUnit lib to your project, use of Maven recommended.

For mac: Shift + CMD + T (or through the tab: Navigate -&gt; Test) to create new test for methods.

In the created class, write method to include test code
<pre>@Test
public void methodNameHere() {
    //codes....
    // For example
    assertEquals(2, new YourClass.someAddMethod(1, 1));
}</pre>
&nbsp;

使用Singleton的好处是只要include了那个类的头文件，就能通过getInstance方法获得类的唯一一个实例，而不用到处传指针之类的东西。
<pre>class Canvas: public PngWriter {
private:
    Canvas(const int width,const int height):PngWriter(width, height){
    }

    // Don't Implement.
    Canvas(Canvas const&amp;);
    void operator=(Canvas const&amp;);

public:
    // Singleton Purpose
    static Canvas&amp; getInstance(int width, int height)
    {
        static Canvas instance(width, height);
        return instance;
    }
};</pre>
展示了可传参数的getInstance，而且只有第一次传进去的参数有效。

Following is a simple demo showing how to pass value between Views using segue in a iOS app.

<!--more-->
<h2>0. Complete the first View Controller</h2>
Here I am using the BMI Calculator to make things easier.

Components and codes are shown below.

<img class="alignnone  wp-image-227" src="https://wth687.files.wordpress.com/2017/03/e5b18fe5b995e5bfabe785a7-2017-03-03-10-23-41.png" alt="屏幕快照 2017-03-03 10.23.41.png" width="201" height="368" />
<pre>import UIKit

class ViewController: UIViewController {
    var BMI: Float = 0
    @IBOutlet weak var inputWeight: UITextField!
    @IBOutlet weak var inputHeight: UITextField!
    @IBOutlet weak var labelResult: UILabel!

    @IBAction func onButtonClicked(_ sender: Any) {
        let weight = Float(inputWeight.text!)!
        let height = Float(inputHeight.text!)!
        BMI = weight / (height * height)

        labelResult.text = “\(BMI)”
    }

    // Default functions being left out
}
</pre>
<h2>1. Create second View Controller</h2>
Open Main.storyboard, drag and drop another View Controller into the storyboard.

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-234" src="https://wth687.files.wordpress.com/2017/03/e5b18fe5b995e5bfabe785a7-2017-03-03-10-19-49.png" alt="屏幕快照 2017-03-03 10.19.49.png" width="1540" height="1276" />

Create another .swift file for the second View Controller

<img class="alignnone  wp-image-239" src="https://wth687.files.wordpress.com/2017/03/e5b18fe5b995e5bfabe785a7-2017-03-03-10-27-33.png" alt="屏幕快照 2017-03-03 10.27.33.png" width="398" height="145" />

Tell the View Controller to use the .swift file you just created as codes behind it.

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-242" src="https://wth687.files.wordpress.com/2017/03/e5b18fe5b995e5bfabe785a7-2017-03-03-10-29-15.png" alt="屏幕快照 2017-03-03 10.29.15.png" width="2462" height="594" />
<h2>2. Create segue between two ViewControllers</h2>
Hold down "control" key on your keyboard, select the button in the first View and drag to the second View, click "Show" as action in the popup window. you should have created a directional segue from First to Second:

<img class="alignnone  wp-image-248" src="https://wth687.files.wordpress.com/2017/03/e5b18fe5b995e5bfabe785a7-2017-03-03-10-36-22.png" alt="屏幕快照 2017-03-03 10.36.22.png" width="453" height="248" />

Then give this segue an identifier:

Select the blue line connecting two Views in the Attributes Inspector on the upper right corner of Xcode. Fill in a unique identifier for this Segue:

<img class="alignnone  wp-image-253" src="https://wth687.files.wordpress.com/2017/03/e5b18fe5b995e5bfabe785a7-2017-03-03-10-38-32.png" alt="屏幕快照 2017-03-03 10.38.32.png" width="376" height="212" />
<h2>3. Add codes to pass value</h2>
Add the following code to the FIRST View's swift file, i.e ViewController.swift
<ol>
	<li>Add the following in the callback func of button</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">self</span><span class="s2">.</span><span class="s3">performSegue</span><span class="s2">(withIdentifier: </span><span class="s4">"showResult"</span><span class="s2">, sender: </span><span class="s1">self</span><span class="s2">)</span></p>
</blockquote>
2. And Overrides a function called prepare
<pre>
override func prepare(for segue: UIStoryboardSegue, sender: Any?) {
    if segue.identifier == “showResult” {
        if let dest = segue.destination as? ViewController2 {
            dest.val = BMI
        }
    }
}
</pre>
Now the val member in the ViewController2.swift will be assigned when the segue is activated.

Here is a sample code for ViewController2.swift:
<pre>
import UIKit

class ViewController2: UIViewController {
    @IBOutlet weak var result: UILabel!
    var val: Float = 0

    override func viewDidLoad() {
        super.viewDidLoad()
        // Do any additional setup after loading the view.

        result.text = String(format:“%.2f”,val)
        if val &lt; 18.5 {
            result.textColor = UIColor.orange
        } else if val &lt; 24.99 {
            result.textColor = UIColor.green
        } else {
            result.textColor = UIColor.red
        }
    }

    override func didReceiveMemoryWarning() {
        super.didReceiveMemoryWarning()

        // Dispose of any resources that can be recreated.
    }
}
</pre>
